Description: Fragment of oval handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbol. Clay fine light brown; distinct red-brown core; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Common stamp. Petrie drew several (EES Archive XVII). Name Antimachos. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0384.16.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0804)
